text: Kundryak () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Kundryaksky Selsoviet, Sterlibashevsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 321 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located 26 km from Sterlibashevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Sterlibashevsky District
title: Kundryak
